The paper discusses reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also mentions deep learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper focuses on general reinforcement learning, which involves learning in unknown environments, and explores different properties of agents, which could fall under multi-agent systems (cs.MA) or control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper presents a software demo, which could fall under robotics (cs.RO) as it involves implementing and testing algorithms in various environments.
